$ SQLPATH - drop_if_exists
@ drop_if_exists.sql

`drop_if_exists.sql` is an SQL script to be run in → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus to drop an
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects[object] (not only a table) if the object exists.

The script is run like so. Note that the object type is not specified:
code {
@drop_if_exists sales_2018
code }

{ Script

  gh|Oracle-SQLPATH|/drop_if_exists.sql||

}

sa:

  The → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement/verbs/drop[SQL verb `drop`]

  The → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement/if-exists[`create … if not exists` and `drop … if exists` clause] in → development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/23c[Oracle 23c].

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath
